race.comment: Moonee Valley may not be ideal for TRES MAGNIFIQUE (12) but her last start effort in a strong race at Caulfield was excellent. She was taken right back on the fence, was badly held up and got going late for fifth behind Point Barrow. If she's kept out of trouble she can round these up. PROFICIENT (10) is a well-bred filly who was heavily backed to score on debut at Sandown Hillside over 1000m, showing fight to prevail narrowly. Up in trip and possibly with something to chase from the plum draw can see her elevate significantly. ROHESIA (4) is going well this time in, just missing here last time out. She'll land in a good spot and can figure. TEINE AULELEI (7) has ability, just not sure where she gets to from the draw.
